      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:anchor>15888</fr:anchor>
        <fr:title text="Contributions">Contributions</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="frankstajano.xml" title="Frank Stajano" addr="frankstajano" type="local">Frank Stajano</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="andrewpitts.xml" title="Andrew Pitts" addr="andrewpitts" type="local">Andrew Pitts</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>9</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>15886</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00OD</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00OD.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Soundness of the subset construction">Soundness of the subset construction</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an NFA with <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>-transitions</html:span>; then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\subseteq  \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>7664</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/998</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>unstable-998.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="" />
                <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>We must show that any string <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> lies in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>7662</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/999</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-999.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Empty string">Empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, then by definition we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\in F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> and so by definition, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>. By definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, we therefore have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\xRightarrow {\epsilon }q]]></fr:tex>; because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \in \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>7663</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="machine">unstable/1000</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>unstable-1000.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Non-empty string">Non-empty string</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>Suppose on the other hand that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=a_1\cdots  a_n]]></fr:tex>, and so we therefore have transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {a_1}S_1\xrightarrow {\ldots }S_{n-1}\xrightarrow {a_n}S_n]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_n\in  F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, and so there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  S_n\cap  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>. Define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0 = s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                    <fr:p>By definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, from the transition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_{n-1}\xrightarrow {a_n}S_n]]></fr:tex> we may find some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{n-1}\in  S_{n-1}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{n-1}\xRightarrow {a_n}q_n]]></fr:tex>. Iterating this process, we may find states <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_i\in  S_{i}]]></fr:tex> such that we have a sequence of transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_{i-1}\xRightarrow {a_i}q_i]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>; thus we have a sequence of transitions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_0\xRightarrow {u}q_n]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_0\in  S_0=s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {\epsilon }q_0]]></fr:tex> and thus <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {\epsilon }q_0\xRightarrow {u}q_n]]></fr:tex> and therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {u} q_n]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q_n\in  F_{M}]]></fr:tex>, we are done.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
